STP.description: Stop- When STP is set to 1 during multiple block transfer, CMD12 is issued to halt the transfer through the SD host interface.However, if a command sequence is halted because of a communications error or timeout, CMD12 is not issued. Although continued buffer access is possible even after STP has been set to 1, the buffer access error bit (ERR5 or ERR4) in SD_INFO2 will be set accordingly.- When STP has been set to 1 during transfer for single block write, the access end flag is set when SD_BUF becomes empty, and CMD12 is not issued. If SD_BUF does contain data, the access end flag is set on completion of reception of the busy state without CMD12 having been issued.- When STP has been set to 1 during transfer for single block read, the access end flag is set immediately after setting of the STP bit and CMD12 is not issued.- When STP is set to 1 during reception of the busy state after an R1b response, the access end flag is set on completion of reception of the busy state without CMD12 having been issued.- When STP is set to 1 after a command sequence has been completed, CMD12 is not issued and the access end flag is not set.- Set STP to 1 after the response end flag has been set.- Set STP to 0 after the response end flag has been set.

MEMMIRADDR.description: Specifies the memory mirror address.NOTE: A value cannot be set in the low-order 7 bits. These bits are fixed to 0.

RRS.description: DTC Transfer Information Read Skip Enable.

DTCVBR.description: DTC Vector Base Address.Note: A value cannot be set in the lower-order 10 bits. These bits are fixed to 0.

VECN.description: DTC-Activating Vector Number MonitoringThese bits indicate the vector number for the activating source when DTC transfer is in progress.The value is only valid if DTC transfer is in progress (the value of the ACT flag is 1)

DBGSTOP_RECCR.description: Mask bit for RAM ECC error reset/interrupt

DBGSTOP_RPER.description: Mask bit for RAM parity error reset/interrupt

DBGSTOP_LVD.description: b18:  Mask bit for LVD2 reset/interrupt (0:enable / 1:Mask)b17:  Mask bit for LVD1 reset/interrupt (0:enable / 1:Mask)b16:  Mask bit for LVD0 reset             (0:enable / 1:Mask)

ENETBFULL.description: Enable bit for halt request by ETB full

ELSEGR%s.description: Event Link Software Event Generation Register %s

WDTRR.description: WDTRR is an 8-bit register that  refreshes the down-counter of the WDT.

CNTVAL.description: Down-Counter ValueValue counted by the down-counter

KRMD.description: Usage of Key Interrupt Flags(KR0 to KR7)

DOPCF.description: Data Operation Circuit FlagIndicates the result of an operation.

DODIR.description: 16-bit read-write register in which 16-bit data for use in the operations are stored.

DODSR.description: This register stores 16-bit data for use as a reference in data comparison mode. This register also stores the results of operations in data addition and data subtraction modes.

TCSS.description: Measurement Target Clock Frequency Division Ratio Select

RCDS.description: Measurement Reference Clock Frequency Division Ratio Select

CAULVR.description: CAULVR is a 16-bit readable/writable register that stores the upper-limit value of the frequency.

CALLVR.description: CALLVR is a 16-bit readable/writable register that stores the lower-limit value of the frequency.

CACNTBR.description: CACNTBR is a 16-bit read-only register that retains the counter value at the time a valid reference signal edge is input
